    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/05318684120602201795" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Sasha</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2014/01/a-good-person-to-know/#comment-41350"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2014-01-12T23:03:17-05:00">Sunday, January 12, 2014 at 11:03 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>In &#39;The Breakfast Book&#39; Marion Cunningham recommends toasting oats in the oven for a few minutes before simmering them on the stove with water to make oatmeal. Toasting the oats in butter indeed sounds like the deluxe, luxurious version. </p>
<p>Cannot wait to call this breakfast tomorrow! </p>
    </div>

