    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>This is delicious! I&#39;ve made it twice now, first with 1% milk (because that&#39;s what we always drink), and then with whole milk (because it was on hand from another recipe). It turned out much better with 1%, though &#8211; the whole milk made quite a skin and didn&#39;t seem to get absorbed into the oats as well. Also, I didn&#39;t think it added a &#8220;richness&#8221; that I&#39;d expected versus the 1%. Thoughts, Molly? Do you use the whole milk for June, or do you prefer it? Btw, your girl is ADORABLE! Also, yes, I can confirm this recipe can be made with a baby on the hip. Lol!</p>
